## Architecture

```
athena/
├── tools/
│   ├── data/                      # Week 1 — data spine
│   │   ├── contract.py            # canonical schemas + validation
│   │   ├── symbols.py             # canonical symbol scheme
│   │   ├── cache.py               # local cache (parquet/feather/pickle)
│   │   ├── router.py              # cache-aware single entry point
│   │   ├── ccxt_adapter.py        # crypto via Binance/CCXT
│   │   ├── delta_adapter.py       # Delta Exchange spot/perps/options
│   │   └── dhan_adapter.py        # Dhan HQ v2 (NSE/BSE/MCX)
│   └── research/                  # Week 2 — research stack
│       ├── runs.py                # immutable run dirs + RunStore
│       ├── stats.py               # Sharpe, Sortino, deflated Sharpe
│       ├── backtest_vbt.py        # vectorbt — for sweeps
│       └── backtest_bt.py         # backtrader — for fills
├── agent/                         # Week 2 — agent infra
│   ├── store.py                   # SQLite: runs, evals, memories, skills
│   └── llm.py                     # OpenRouter client + cheap/smart routing
├── tests/                         # 35/35 passing, no network needed
├── skills/                        # markdown, agent-writable (Week 3)
├── data/                          # parquet cache + immutable run records
└── pipeline/                      # one folder per research idea
```

The **canonical data contract** is the keystone. Every adapter returns frames
with the exact same shape — UTC-aware timestamps, canonical symbols
(`NSE:RELIANCE`, `DELTA:BTCUSD`, `BINANCE:BTC/USDT`). Everything downstream
speaks this dialect. Strategies portable across asset classes for free.

The **deflated Sharpe** is the second non-obvious choice. Naive Sharpe
overstates alpha when you sweep parameters, and the agent will sweep
parameters. Without DSR, the agent surfaces false positives confidently.
With it, it doesn't.

The **immutable run records** are the third. Every backtest gets a
content-addressed directory under `data/backtests/<run_id>/` that's never
modified. Same params → same run_id → answerable "have I tested this"
even after months of work.

---

## Tests

```bash
# All tests are network-free. Set the cache backend to pickle if you don't
# have pyarrow installed.
ATHENA_CACHE_FORMAT=pickle python -m pytest athena/tests/ -v
```

Or run individually:

```bash
python athena/tests/test_data_spine.py        # 7 tests
python athena/tests/test_stats.py             # 17 tests
python athena/tests/test_runs_and_store.py    # 10 tests
python athena/tests/test_e2e_pipeline.py      # 1 test
```

The end-to-end test wires the data router, signal computation, stats, run
storage, and SQLite registry into one pipeline — no network, no LLM, no
backtest engines. If it passes, the spine is sound.

---

## Roadmap

- **Week 1 (done)** — Data spine: contract, symbols, cache, three adapters, router.
- **Week 2 (done)** — Research stack: stats, runs, vectorbt + backtrader, SQLite, OpenRouter LLM client.
- **Week 3** — Agent loop: tool registry, skill system, background review fork, Telegram gateway, sandboxed Python REPL.
- **Week 4** — Live signal monitoring with cron + first knowledge ingestion source (arXiv q-fin).
- **Week 5** — Modal sandbox for heavy backtests, news/filing ingestion, weekly digest generation.
- **Week 6+** — The Curator (skill consolidation), walk-forward harness, paper trading hookup.

---

## Honest caveats

- **Dhan instrument master.** Column names shift occasionally; `_resolve()` in
  `dhan_adapter.py` is the most fragile piece. Patch when needed.
- **Delta dated-futures naming** isn't fully consistent across the API surface.
  Common cases handled; edges will surface.
- **Live intraday cache.** The current bar updates between fetches. Flush the
  last bar's timestamp before trusting it for live signals (Week 4 problem).
- **vectorbt vs backtrader stats** won't match exactly — different fill models.
  That's intentional (vectorbt for screening, backtrader for validation), but
  cross-engine comparisons need care.
- **Deflated Sharpe assumes i.i.d. trial Sharpes.** Reality is correlated.
  The correction is conservative when trials are correlated. Treat `dsr > 0.95`
  as necessary but not sufficient — pair with walk-forward (Week 3).
- **The agent will get trade ideas wrong.** Treat its outputs as a junior
  analyst's. Your job is still oversight. Athena alerts; it doesn't trade.

